Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Court reporter Teri Groves. Defendant Delliyano C Black in court, in custody.  Attorney Marshall Lemaster Belton in court for Delliyano C Black.  Attorney Colleen Lennon in court for State of Wisconsin. In court for a competency hearing. State gives statement. Atty Belton makes statement.  Dr K. Jackson is duly sworn and testifies. State with direct exam. Dr Jacksons report at docket 14 is marked offered and received. Atty Belton with cross exam. State with redirect. Dr. Jackson is excused. Defendant Ms. Black is duly sworn and testifies. Atty Belton with direct exam. No cross by the State. Court makes ruling and for reasons stated on the record finds the defendant not competent. Court to sign order.
